JOHANNESBURG - Mortimer Saunders has pleaded guilty in the Western Cape High Court to the murder of three-year-old Courtney Pieters. But he insists it was not premeditated. Saunders denied raping Pieters but he admitted to having sex with her corpse. He had been living in a room in the house rented by the girl’s parents in Cape Town's Elsies River at the time of the murder last year. His plea explanation contained shocking details of what took place on the day the toddler died. READ: Wreath laying ceremony for 3-year-old Courtney Pieters The girl was reported missing on 4 May 2017, with her body found only days later, buried in a shallow grave. Saunders declined bail, saying he feared for his life. eNCA